About the job
Company Mission
narb is an early-stage startup committed to pioneering accessible and open-source technology solutions. Following a strategic infusion of capital from a visionary investor, we have accelerated our mission to democratize cutting-edge technology. We are currently developing narba, an innovative outbound AI voice-call assistant capable of making simultaneous calls using the user’s own voice. At narb, we value creativity, openness, and proactive initiative as we strive to create technology that truly enhances everyday life.

We’re seeking talented, driven interns eager to make an immediate, tangible impact from day one. Join our engineering team and play a central role in shaping the future of human-like voice-driven automation

Build robust mobile and web interfaces for narba using React Native, Next.js, and TypeScript.
Implement front-end components and integrate APIs to manage real-time voice interactions and dynamic user experiences.
Contribute actively to architectural decisions around voice-processing integrations and AI-driven outbound call workflows.
Develop and maintain reliable, secure, and scalable applications tailored to AI-driven conversational and voice-call technology.
Collaborate closely with machine learning and UX interns to ensure smooth integration of AI voice models and seamless user experience.
Document and share your technical insights through weekly LinkedIn or developer-blog updates.
Participate actively in sprint meetings, code reviews, and agile development processes.

Undergraduate student pursuing majors in:
Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Technology, or related technical fields
Electrical & Computer Engineering, Computational Linguistics, or Data Science
Digital Media, Cognitive Science, or Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) with a strong technical foundation
Required technical proficiencies:
Strong hands-on experience in React Native, Next.js, and TypeScript

Experience with Git/GitHub, CI/CD workflows, and agile methodologies
Excellent debugging, testing, and documentation skills
Highly motivated, organized, reliable, and able to deliver consistently within tight deadlines
Effective communication skills and ability to collaborate cross-functionally

Familiarity with Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), vector databases (e.g., Pinecone, pgvector, Chroma, Weaviate)
Knowledge of AI voice models and voice-agent frameworks (e.g., Whisper, VALL-E, Eleven Labs, OpenAI TTS)

WHY JOIN US
Direct involvement in pioneering an AI-driven voice-call assistant poised to redefine user interactions at scale
Leveraging stable investment capital, you’ll work within a creative environment optimized for rapid innovation
Receive personalized mentorship and collaboration opportunities from dedicated startup founders and experienced engineers
Build high-impact portfolio projects and develop professional networks across technology leaders
Enjoy a flexible remote work environment designed for asynchronous collaboration
Initial internship unpaid, with clear pathways to performance-based incentives and future paid roles as the company scales
